JAVASCRIPT statements
a javascript stament is basically lines of codes.
We use semi-colon(;) to end statements in javascript.

Types of variable keywords
1. var - it was abandoned in 2015, becuase it escapes the function and becomes
a global variable. it has the ability to be called outside the scope and this can 
cause errors in creating a function or a piece of code.
A scope is created inside a curly brace and the code inside of it doesn't have
any business outside that curly brace.
var can be reasigned a value, let can be reassigned a value but const cannot be reassigned a value
assognment operators(=) are used to give a value to a variable. 
in a block scope any code in the culry braces is not affected by an external line of code.
CONST IN JAVASCRIPT
constants are values in javascript that there value cannot be changed by reassginment.
a constant cannot be reassigned and redeclared.

