Increment operators 
addition Increment operator - ++ - increase the value of a variable by 1
subtraction decrement operator - -- - decreases the value of a variable by 1
exponentiation(raise to power) - ** can also be replaced by math.pow(x,y)

COMPARISON OPERATORS.
The comparison operators is used to compare two or more values. 
we have the following types of comparsion operators.
 ==   -this is used to compare the how equal two values are.
 ===  -this is used to compare both the type and value of a variable.
 !=   -this is the not equal operator used to chack if a values is not equal.
 !==  -this is used to check if the values and type of a data is not equal.
 >    -this is the greater than symbol used to check if a value is greater than the other.
 <    -this is the lesser than symbol used to check if a value is lesser than the other.
 >=   -this is the greater than symbol used to check if a value is greater or equal than the other.
 <=   -this is the lesser than symbol used to check if a value is lesser or equal than the other.

