ARRAYS (LISTS) IN JAVASCRIPT
An array is a special variable that can store multiple values.

ARRAY INDEX 
Is the position of items inside an array(lists).

ARRAY METHODS
AN ARRAY METHOD IS USED TO MANIPULATE AN ARRAY OR CARRY OUT AN ACTION ON IT.
They usually end with a closed bracket.
EXAMPLES.
-push() - Adds to the end.
-pop()  - Removes the last item.
unshift() - Adds to the beginning.
shift() -Removes first item.

